NUMBER 649
REGION 50
FIXED_LIGHT
NAME Cloud tops, river bed
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
You find yourself standing up to your knees in water in a strange cloud top river that extends out of sight to the east and west. The current of the river tugs you toward another cloud layer below to the east. A formation of upswept clouds leads to another layer above. A periodical barrage of lightning and thunder strikes rumble the 'ground' every few moments. A cloud 'bridge' spans the sky over your head.
*DESCRIPTION_END
CHANNEL 92
IFENTRY
  ECHO PLAYER You feel something brush up against your leg.
ENDIF
ASTRAL
EXIT E 681
EXIT W 678
EXIT U 665
RANDOM DUMMY1 1 20 0
IFVAR DUMMY1 = 3
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
    ECHO PLAYER The cloud rumbles violenty and you are knocked down into the river.
    ECHO OTHERS %N is knocked down as the cloud rumbles.
    POSITION LAY
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB SIT -1
  EQUAL FLAG1 1
ENDIF
IFVERB STAND -1
  EQUAL FLAG1 1
ENDIF
;
;
NUMBER 653
REGION 50
FIXED_LIGHT
NAME Cloud tops
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Around you the mist has swirled onto a single plane forming a sort of circular field. Above you through other layers of clouds a brilliant sun shines down on the fluffy white surface around you. In the center of this field, sharp white flashes of light brighten around a central hole. Peering through it you can see endless space and a myriad of twinkling stars.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ASTRAL
EXIT N 692
EXIT E 690
EXIT S 689
EXIT W 691
CHANNEL 92
MONSTER_GROUP 68
ITEM 0 431
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM IN 0
You see the fathomless realms of eternity.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB GO 0
	CLEARVERB
	ECHO PLAYER You just can't let yourself suffer a fate worse than death for all eternity.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB2 PUT 0
	ECHO PLAYER You put %a in %b and it falls away for eternity.
	ECHO OTHERS %N puts %a in %b and watches disappear from sight.
	GMSG %N is an idiot.
ENDIF
